reviews.text: Happy meal set is no wonder the cheapest and funny meal for kids.

This McDonald's has friendly service, good quality food, and good portion sizes. The only downside to this McDonald is the ridiculous amount of people there. On a good day, you could wait for a good 5 to 10 minutes, on a busy day you could be waiting there for up to 20 maybe even 30 minutes(very rare usually lunch hour).
The McDonald's at Cityplaza I Level 5 is good enough to get by. It has in addition a Mccafe. The staff is okay. The food and beverage are standard.

Awful fried chicken here — the worst I've ever had. I came in with certain expectations because I love the Stanley McDonald's fried chicken, but I was in for an unpleasant surprise. They're considerably smaller, extremely oily (not crisp at all), and has a weird fishy aftertaste (for the same price as the delicious ones in Stanley). There are most definitely better alternatives to McDonald's in CityPlaza. Looking for a meal? I recommend Mango Tree Cafe or the Japanese restaurant next to that. Looking to grab a snack? There's Starbucks/Pacific Coffee there too.
A lot were patronizing these fastfood which really great for everybody. Service crew were polite and helpful too

result.name: 麥當勞

reviews.text: 十號風球都開👍

我點了薯條走鹽及朱古力雪糕新地少朱古力醬。 在排自動點餐機的時候已經覺得好奇怪：店中共有七部點餐機，卻只開啟了三只。當去等餐點的時候，終於都了解狀況：只望入開放式的廚房，只有寥寥幾個人忙呀忙。 (好明顯係冇人手唔敢開咁多部機驚做唔切)等了五分鐘雪糕及薯條都有喇。我準備吃的時候，我拎收那份薯條，整包都是涼的！！ 既不是剛剛炸起油淋淋，就好像是炸完之後一直掛在爐邊，掛到什麼油份及什麼溫度也沒有就包起給我...因為新鮮即炸起走鹽的薯條，該有一點炸起之後的餘溫。 但這包白白亮亮真真正正走鹽的薯條，總好過同一個購物中心內某連鎖漢堡包店那些又粗又大又愛番炸又超多鹽的細薯條。
今期麥當勞引入新口味薑味汽水：這個我很鍾意的.今日試飲,真係掂喎!不過我要多冰,因為唔想飲得咁濃/甜。食魚柳蝦堡都要少醬,因為冇嗌到其他炸嘅嘢,所以整體食落都唔錯.只係等食物嘅時間好明顯真係有啲耐~~~ 怪唔得而家叫嘅係麥當勞餐廳：因為等嘢食嘅時間已經與快餐無緣了...
太古城中心5樓。新裝修，職員出食物效率高，但執枱慢。
差! 用來包住豬柳蛋包的紙，篤穿了!都交畀客人!真要檢討!!!

result.name: Cityplaza

reviews.text:
Many different stores for people to buy stuff from. There's an ice skating rink and many people go there to play.

The mall is close to the MTR station, which makes it very convenient to reach. There is also a park nearby.

This was the biggest mall I ever visited. Free wifi. Public transport right outside the main entrance doors. Everything you need under one roof. Restaurants around every corner so you can't go wrong. Will definitely go back.

Shopping here is not for the faint of heart. Fill thy wallet and endure queues of long.
From left and to right, shall your eyes dart.
Your purchases a burden, arms strong.

The food court has a variety of Japanese related food items and it is all delicious and fast delivery. The food quality matches the food prices. Only issue is it gets very crowded during lunch hours other than that, a great experience.

This is now a very large mall after its extension. Not only it is big where you could almost get anything what other malls offer, it is also very spacious without the crazy crowds(yet) probably due to its location which is still very much an residential area. Though slightly off the shopping belt, it is very easily accessible by the MTR.
